File: Auditing. Pixabay/Stee Buissinne JOHANNESBURG - Newly-appointed Independent Regulatory Board of Auditors (IRBA) CEO Jenitha John has resigned. Her appointment to head up the auditing watchdog was controversial due to her previous role at Tongaat Hulett. READ: Auditors must rebuild trust in profession John's resignation comes less than three weeks after Finance Minister Tito Mboweni dissolved the regulator's board. Although never accused of wrongdoing, John had been a board member at Tongaat where she chaired the audit committee when accounting irregularities emerged at the company.